    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Rinse your<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-sausage-and-black-bean-stew-with-brown-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>sausages</strong> into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped sausages </strong>and cook for 4-5 min or until they're browned</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-sausage-and-black-bean-stew-with-brown-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>red onion[s]</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-sausage-and-black-bean-stew-with-brown-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the sausage has begun to brown, add the <strong>sliced onion </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and 1/2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3/4 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to soften</p><p>Once slightly softened, add your <strong>southern fried seasoning </strong>and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-sausage-and-black-bean-stew-with-brown-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash your<strong> spinach </strong>and pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Drain and rinse your <strong>black beans</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-sausage-and-black-bean-stew-with-brown-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong>, <strong>chopped tomatoes</strong>, <strong>drained black beans </strong>and <strong>spinach </strong>with 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[250ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium-high and and cook for 6-7 min or until the sauce begins to thicken to a gravy-like consistency and the sausages are cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>smoky sausage & black bean stew</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-sausage-and-black-bean-stew-with-brown-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Grate your <strong>lighter cheese</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-sausage-and-black-bean-stew-with-brown-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>smoky sausage & black bean stew </strong>over the <strong>cooked rice</strong></p><p>Top with the <strong>grated cheese</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
